You are only updating languages. Following are some descriptions and examples of different ways to use the language property in a description. Use these as a reference when updating language in the description.

## "language" model
Language refers to the language of the resource being described, For the language of the metadata, use valueLanguage.

| Property | Definition | Value type | Repeatable |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| value | Value of the descriptive element. | String| No |
| code | Code value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| status | Status of the language relative to other parallel language elements (e.g. the primary language). | String | No |
| uri | URI value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| standard | Descriptive or content standard to which the value conforms. | Object ("standard" model) | No |
| encoding | Encoding schema, standard, or syntax to which the value conforms. | Object ("encoding" model) | No |
| source | The vocabulary, authority, or other origin for the language term and/or code. | Object ("source" model) | No |
| displayLabel | The preferred display label to use for the descriptive element in access systems. | String | No |
| qualifier | A term providing information about the circumstances of the statement. | String | No |
| note | Other information about the language of the resource. Note types must be from the "note" controlled list. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| valueLanguage | Language of the descriptive metadata value. | Object ("value language" model) | No |
| script | An alphabet or other notation used to represent a language or other symbolic system associated with the resource. | Object ("description" model) | No |
| appliesTo | Portion or aspect of the resource the value applies to. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| structuredValue | Multiple values intended to be concatenated in order to form a single value. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| parallelValue | Multiple representations of the same information, such as in different languages. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| groupedValue | For interoperability with MODS. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| valueAt | URI or other pointer to the location of the language information. | String | No |

### Basic language

For language terms, codes, and URIs, the ISO 639-2b standard is preferred. See the list of all ISO 639-2b languages (https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/iso639-2.html).

```json
{
  "language": [
    {
      "value": "Arabic",
      "code": "ara",
      "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/iso639-2/ara",
      "source": {
        "code": "iso639-2b"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### Language and script

For scripts terms and codes, the ISO 15924 standard is preferred. See the list of all ISO 15924 scripts (https://www.unicode.org/iso15924/iso15924-codes.html).

```json
{
  "language": [
    {
      "value": "Korean",
      "code": "kor",
      "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/iso639-2/kor",
      "source": {
        "code": "iso639-2b"
      },
      "script": {
        "value": "Korean",
        "code": "Kore",
        "source": {
          "code": "iso15924"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```


### Language applying to part of the resource

```json
{
  "language": [
    {
      "value": "Italian",
      "code": "ita",
      "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/iso639-2/ita",
      "source": {
        "code": "iso639-2b"
      },
      "appliesTo": [
        {
          "value": "liner notes"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
